# PII audit exemptions (Presidio + coordinated secret scans).
# Gitignore-style syntax. Also read as .ignorepii if present.
#
# IMPORTANT: .piiignore is OPT-IN only. Scanners ignore it by default.
# Pass --observe-piiignore to audit_pii.py / audit_secrets.py / check_secrets.py
# to honor these exemptions. Pre-commit never passes that flag — commit content
# is always scanned. Forbidden paths (.kb/, .venv/) always alarm if staged.
#
# PII-REVIEWED ACKNOWLEDGMENT LANE (fail-closed with evidence):
#   Pre-commit still scans everything. A PII finding on a path listed HERE (and not
#   forbidden) is not silently skipped — it is deferred to the commit-msg hook, which
#   BLOCKS unless the commit message carries a substantive trailer:
#       PII-Reviewed: <why these are false positives / safe fixtures>
#   One trailer per commit covers that commit's exemptible findings. Only paths in this
#   file are acknowledgeable; secrets and forbidden paths (.env, .kb/) always hard-block.
#   Prefer explaining each exemption inline below so reviewers see the justification.
#
# RULE: every path here MUST also be in .gitignore (or be a safe *.example template).

# ── Local career vault & runtime (gitignored) ────────────────────────────────
agentic/hermes/.kb/
.kb/
agentic/hermes/.generated/
agentic/hermes/.runtime/
.cache/
career_kb/

# ── Virtualenv / tooling ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.venv/
venv/
__pycache__/

# ── Fixtures & safe templates ────────────────────────────────────────────────
tests/
tests/fixtures/
tests/data/
**/*.example.json
**/*.example.yaml
**/*.example.yml
**/*.local.yaml.example
.env.example
agentic/hermes/kb/scaffold/

# ── Documented machine / dependency files (no real PII) ───────────────────────
agentic/hermes/admin/config/hermes_roles.yaml
requirements.txt
requirements-*.txt

# ── Hook docs (agent attribution examples) ───────────────────────────────────
.githooks/

# detect-secrets baseline (hashed audit state)
.secrets.baseline
